2 - Calculate normalized expression

Normalize data following Alba et al 2014 method

To normalize we: - calculate the average between the three replicates - Calculate the normalized cq values by using the following formula (1/(2gene))/(1/(1.8reference gene)) where the value for the efficacy of each gene is 2 for PIIC and PPOD, 1.8 for actin and PR1a - Find the minimum value for each gene and divide all data by it to normalize the data

sum_df<-df %>%
  group_by(Plant, Treatment, Sample_code) %>%
  summarise(mean_Actin=mean(Actin, na.rm=TRUE),mean_PIIIc=mean(PI.IIc, na.rm=TRUE), mean_PPOD=mean(PPO.D, na.rm=TRUE), mean_PR1a=mean(PR.1a, na.rm=TRUE)) %>%
  group_by(Plant, Treatment, Sample_code)%>%
  summarise(Cq_PIIIc= (1/(2^mean_PIIIc))/(1/(1.8^mean_Actin)), Cq_PPOD= (1/(2^mean_PPOD))/(1/(1.8^mean_Actin)), Cq_PR1a= (1/(1.8^mean_PR1a))/(1/(1.8^mean_Actin))) %>%
  as.data.frame()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Plant', 'Treatment'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Plant', 'Treatment'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
sum_df
# Normalize by minimum value of each gene

minPIIIc<-min(sum_df$Cq_PIIIc, na.rm=TRUE)
minPPOD<-min(sum_df$Cq_PPOD, na.rm=TRUE)
minPR1a<-min(sum_df$Cq_PR1a, na.rm=TRUE)

sum_df$NE_PIIIc<-sum_df$Cq_PIIIc/minPIIIc
sum_df$NE_PPOD<-sum_df$Cq_PPOD/minPPOD
sum_df$NE_PR1a<-sum_df$Cq_PR1a/minPR1a
